article.description: Shaunte Smith scored 20 points, Andrea Riley added 14, and Oklahoma State (No. 24 ESPN/USA Today, No. 21 AP) beat North Texas 80-54 in a sloppy game that featured 57 turnovers.
article.headline: Oklahoma State beats North Texas in game with 57 turnovers
article.linkText: Okla. St. wins sloppy matchup with North Texas
article.story:
STILLWATER, Okla. -- Shaunte Smith scored 20 points, Andrea Riley added 14, and Oklahoma State (No. 24 ESPN/USA Today, No. 21 AP) beat North Texas 80-54 on Sunday in a sloppy game that featured 57 turnovers.

Amber Jackson and Brittney James opened the second half with field goals to get North Texas (5-7) within 14, but the Mean Green would get no closer the rest of the way.

Taylor Hardeman and Ally Clardy each had a pair of 3-pointers as Oklahoma State extended its lead to 65-35, and the Cowgirls (9-2) went on to win their 30th straight home non-conference game.

Kristin Hernandez added 11 points and Tegan Cunningham had 10 points and 11 rebounds for Oklahoma State.

James led North Texas with 11 points, and Jackson saw her streak of eight straight double-doubles end with a 10-point, six-rebound performance.
